<L>__{exterior kigali soccer stadium. day}
<A>__{the trucks crawl into the chaos of the stadium, a mass of refugees, the wounded, lost children, abandoned old people, hundreds crammed together. paul, tatiana, and the others clamber off the trucks. they hug, cry, an outpouring of relief. then tatiana spots someone among the crowds. she rushes over.}
<C>__{tatiana}
<D>__{have you seen my sister fedens?}
<A>__{heads shak `no'. tatiana moves on, more frantic, pushing through the crowds.}
<C>__{tatiana}
<D>__{two little girls, twins, an old woman had them.}
<A>__{more `nos' now she's desperate, pushing, tripping through the crowds, and around her we see others doing the same, then}
<C>__{oger }
